      role="U.S. District Court, Eastern District of Michigan"
      detail="110-page sanctions ruling against Sidney Powell's 'Kraken' lawyers · August 2021"
    />
    <VoiceCard
      quote="Contestants did not prove under any standard of proof that any illegal votes were cast and counted, or legal votes were not counted at all."
      name="Judge James T. Russell"
      role="First Judicial District Court, Nevada"
      detail="December 4, 2020"
      context="Used the phrase 'did not prove under any standard of proof' 25 times in his 35-page ruling."
    />
  </VoicesSection>

  <CategoryGrid>
    <CategoryCard
      icon="🏛️"
      title="The Supreme Court Refused to Hear It"
      body="Trump called <em>Texas v. Pennsylvania</em> — filed by AG Ken Paxton — <em>&quot;the big one.&quot;</em> The Supreme Court refused to hear it, ruling Texas had no standing to challenge how other states run elections.<br><br><strong>None of Trump's three Supreme Court appointees</strong> — Gorsuch, Kavanaugh, and Barrett — indicated they saw any merit to the case. Even Justices Alito and Thomas, who said they would have allowed the filing, stated they <em>&quot;would not grant other relief.&quot;</em>"
      tag="All 3 Trump Appointees Rejected It"
    />
    <CategoryCard
      icon="🔨"
      title="Sanctions Against Trump's Lawyers"
      body="Courts didn't just reject the claims — they <strong>punished the lawyers</strong> for bringing them. Sidney Powell and her co-counsel were sanctioned over $175,000 for the Michigan &quot;Kraken&quot; lawsuit. The Supreme Court later upheld these sanctions, refusing to hear Powell's appeal.<br><br>The judge's message was clear: these lawsuits were filed not to win in court, but to <strong>undermine public trust in democracy</strong>."
      tag="$175,000+ in Sanctions"
    />
  </CategoryGrid>

